-- Brazil’s Rousseff Aims at Least 4% Growth in 2012, O Globo Says
-- B y   M a r i a   L u i z a   R a b e l l o
-- 2012-01-08T14:07:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-08/brazil-s-rousseff-aims-at-least-4-growth-in-2012-o-globo-says.html
Brazil ’s president Dilma Rousseff
plans to boost investments and credit in a bid to have the
country’s economy grow at least 4 percent this year,  O Globo 
reported, without saying how it obtained the information.  The government will spend 50 billion reais ($26.9 billion)
to “boost investments” and invest 40 billion reais in state-
controlled banks in order to increase the credit available, the
Rio de Janeiro-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Luiza Rabello in Brasilia at 
 mrabello@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier in New York at 
 swier@bloomberg.net  